## 02 — Architecture Overview

Seatly is two client apps sharing one Supabase backend. There is no separate API server — all backend logic lives in Supabase (PostgreSQL, RLS policies, and Edge Functions).

  ---------------------- --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Layer**              **Technology**

  Web app                Vite + React + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui (keep as-is, wire to Supabase)

  Mobile app             React Native + Expo SDK 52 + TypeScript + NativeWind (not yet started)

  Backend                Supabase — PostgreSQL 17, hosted in ca-central-1 (Canada)

  Auth                   Supabase Auth — email, Google, Apple (iOS only)

  Payments               Stripe Connect — platform takes $1.00 fee, restaurants receive payout

  AI                     Claude API — called only via Supabase Edge Functions, never direct from client

  Maps                   Google Maps API

  Push notifications     Expo Push Notifications (mobile) + in-app + email + SMS

  Storage                Supabase Storage — restaurant-images, menu-item-images, avatars, receipts, exports

  i18n                   i18next — English + French minimum on all user-facing strings
  ---------------------- --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

### One App, Role-Based Routing

Both the web app and mobile app serve all user types from a single codebase. After login, the app reads the user's role and routes accordingly:

  -------------------------------------------- ------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **User type**                                **What they see**

  Customer (no row in user_restaurant_roles)   Customer experience — discover, book, order, loyalty, profile

  Owner                                        Full restaurant dashboard — all pages including billing and settings

  Manager                                      Full dashboard except billing

  Server                                       Floor plan, reservations, orders

  Host                                         Floor plan, reservations, waitlist

  Kitchen                                      Kitchen display system (KDS) only

  Bar                                          Bar orders only

  Staff                                        Schedule and clock in/out only
  -------------------------------------------- ------------------------------------------------------------------------


> **RULE:** Role is determined by user_restaurant_roles table. If NO row exists for a user → they are a customer. If ANY row exists → they are staff and see the staff experience. Customers never see staff screens. Staff never see customer screens.

