### Absolute Rules — Web App

Every developer must follow these on every file, no exceptions:

-   TypeScript everywhere — never use any

-   Never write Supabase queries directly in UI components — always use hooks

-   Never call the Claude API from the client — always go through Edge Functions

-   Never use Claude for financial calculations — hardcoded math only

-   Money in DB is numeric (decimal dollars, e.g. 24.99) — NOT cents integers

-   Always format money with formatCurrency() — never manual string concatenation

-   All user-facing strings go through i18n keys — never hardcode display text

-   All forms use react-hook-form + zod validation

-   Never bypass RLS — every API route validates the JWT

-   File naming: Components = PascalCase, hooks = camelCase with use prefix

-   No hardcoded colour hex values anywhere — use Tailwind tokens only


> **MONEY RULE:** formatCurrency(24.99, "cad") → "$24.99" \| formatCurrency(1250.00, "cad") → "$1,250.00" — import from @/lib/utils/formatCurrency

