### Staff Mobile Screens — Detailed

Each staff screen below must be built. These are the exact screens, their purpose, and what they must contain.

### Floor Plan — staff

Live realtime view of all tables. Colour coded: green = empty, gold = reserved, red = occupied, grey = cleaning. Tapping a table opens a bottom sheet: table number, capacity, current guest name and party size, action buttons (Seat Guest, Mark Cleaning, Clear Table). Hosts seat walk-ins here. Servers see their section.

### Reservations — staff

Today reservations sorted by time. Each row: time, guest name, party size, status chip, special request indicator. Tap to open detail + check in button. Filter chips: All, Upcoming, Seated, Completed. Pull to refresh.

### Orders / KDS — staff

Kitchen Display System. Three columns: Pending, In Progress, Ready. Each card: table number, items with quantity, time since ordered, advance status button. Kitchen marks preparing to ready. Server marks served. Bar role sees drinks only.

### Schedule — staff

Weekly calendar of the logged-in staff member's own shifts. Days across top, shift blocks show start/end time and shift name. Tap a shift for Shift Detail. Week navigation arrows. Staff see own schedule only. Owner/manager can see all staff.

### My Hours — staff

Most important screen for regular staff. Shows: clock in/out button (large, gold, prominent), current status (clocked in at [time] or not clocked in), this week hours table (day, shift, hours worked, pay per shift), total hours this week, estimated pay = hours x hourly_rate from user_restaurant_roles. All pay amounts in CAD via formatCurrency(). Data from staff_clock_records + user_restaurant_roles.hourly_rate.

### Clock In Confirmation — staff

Full screen shown after clocking in. Gold checkmark, Clocked In heading, timestamp (Saturday March 23 at 5:47 PM), shift name if matched to staff_shifts, Done button back to My Hours. Creates staff_clock_records row with clocked_in_at = now().

### Shift Detail — staff

Shown when tapping a shift in Schedule. Shows: restaurant name, date, start and end time, role for shift, confirmed status chip, manager notes, Confirm Shift button (sets confirmed_at), Request Swap button (text field, sends notification to manager). Read-only for past shifts.

### Notifications — staff

All notifications for this staff member from notifications table. Each row: type icon, title, body, time ago. Unread rows have gold left border. Tap marks is_read = true. Pull to refresh. Staff see: shift_reminder (24h before shift), no_show_flag (managers only), waitlist_ready (hosts only), booking_confirmed (if assigned waiter).

### Owner Mobile Dashboard — owner only

KPI overview for owners on the go. Four large KPI cards: tonight covers, today revenue, open orders, no-show risks. Scrollable today reservation timeline below. Simple bar chart of this week covers. AI chat button top right. Read-only — owners do detailed management on web dashboard.

