## 05 — Customer Ordering

Customers can order food through Seatly in three distinct flows. The backend fully supports all three.

### Flow 1 — Pre-Order with Reservation

During the 7-step booking flow (Step 4), customers can browse menu_items where is_preorderable = true and add items to their pre-order. Pre-orders create an order record with is_preorder = true, linked to the reservation via reservations.preorder_order_id. Payment is collected at Step 6 along with any deposit.

### Flow 2 — QR Code Dine-In Ordering

Every table has a qr_code_url stored in the tables table. Scanning the QR code on mobile opens an ordering flow with the full menu (no pre-order filter — all available items). Customer selects items, adds modifier options, reviews cart, and pays via Stripe. The order is created in real-time and fires to the kitchen display. No reservation or account required — guest checkout supported.

### Flow 3 — Online Ordering (Takeout/Pickup/Delivery)

Available on the /[restaurantSlug] web page and mobile. Requires the restaurant to have opted into this service (stored in restaurants.settings_json). Delivery is only available if the restaurant opts in — they use their own drivers, no third-party courier. Takeout and pickup are available immediately when opted in.

### Guest Checkout (No Account Required)

Customers can book reservations and place orders without creating a Seatly account. This applies to all ordering flows. Here is what changes for guest checkout:

-   reservations.is_guest_checkout = true — name, email, phone captured directly on the reservation

-   orders.is_guest_checkout = true — set on any order placed without an account

-   No loyalty points earned — points require a Seatly account linked to a guests record

-   Payment entered manually every time — no saved card, no Stripe customer on file

-   Booking confirmation sent to guest_email on the reservation

-   A guests CRM record is still created for the restaurant so staff can see the booking


  Encourage account creation by surfacing the benefit clearly: "Create an account to earn loyalty points and save your payment method." Never block checkout — just inform.

  -------------------------------- --------------------------------------------------------------
  **Field**                        **Notes**

  orders.is_preorder               true = pre-order tied to reservation

  orders.status                    pending → confirmed → preparing → ready → served → cancelled

  order_items.status               ordered → preparing → ready → served

  order_items.kitchen_started_at   Set when kitchen starts preparing

  order_items.kitchen_ready_at     Set when item is ready to serve

  menu_items.is_preorderable       Only these items show in pre-order step

  menu_items.is_available          86'd items — hide from all ordering flows

  menu_items.is_featured           Show in featured section on restaurant page

  tables.qr_code_url               QR code for dine-in ordering — already generated in DB

  restaurants.settings_json        Controls which ordering options are enabled per restaurant
  -------------------------------- --------------------------------------------------------------

### Delivery

Delivery is optional and fully restaurant-controlled. When a restaurant opts in, they use their own drivers — there is no third-party courier integration. Seatly facilitates the order and payment flow; the restaurant manages fulfilment entirely.

The following delivery fields are now live in the orders table:

-   order_type — text: dine_in \| preorder \| takeout \| delivery (null = legacy dine-in)

-   delivery_address — text: customer delivery address

-   delivery_notes — text: delivery instructions from customer

-   estimated_delivery_at — timestamptz: set by restaurant staff

-   delivery_status — text: pending \| preparing \| ready_for_pickup \| out_for_delivery \| delivered \| failed

-   driver_name — text: restaurant's own driver

-   driver_phone — text: restaurant's own driver phone


  Delivery fields are in the DB. Do not build delivery UI until the restaurant has opted in via settings_json. All delivery rows must have order_type = "delivery" set explicitly.

