## 11 — Payments & Billing

### Stripe Connect

Seatly uses Stripe Connect. Restaurants onboard via the /setup wizard (signup-restaurant-owner edge function creates their Stripe Connect account). Payments split automatically: customer pays → Seatly takes $1.00 platform fee → restaurant receives the rest.

  ------------------------------ ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Field**                      **Where stored**

  Restaurant Stripe account ID   restaurants.stripe_account_id

  Onboarding complete flag       restaurants.stripe_onboarding_complete — must be true before payments work

  Customer Stripe customer ID    user_profiles.stripe_customer_id

  Customer payment method        user_profiles.stripe_payment_method_id

  Guest payment method           guests.stripe_payment_method_id (per-restaurant)

  Platform fee per transaction   $1.00 CAD — payments.platform_fee default 1.00

  Restaurant payout              payments.restaurant_payout = amount - platform_fee
  ------------------------------ ------------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Payment Flows

### Deposit on Booking

If the restaurant has configured a deposit policy (restaurants.deposit_policy_json), a deposit is charged at Step 6 of the booking flow. Amount stored in reservations.deposit_amount. Stripe payment intent stored in reservations.deposit_stripe_payment_intent_id.

### Pre-Order Payment

Pre-order total charged at booking Step 6 along with any deposit. Creates an order record and a payment record with payment_type = preorder.

### Bill Close (Dine-In)

When service is complete, staff trigger the close-bill Edge Function. This calculates the final total (subtotal + tax + tip - discounts - gift cards - loyalty redemptions), charges the customer's saved payment method or prompts for payment, and marks the order paid_at.

### Important Money Rules

-   All prices in DB are numeric decimal dollars (e.g. 24.99) — NOT cents integers

-   Always use formatCurrency(amount, "cad") — never format money manually

-   Never use Claude/AI for financial calculations — hardcoded math only

-   Tax rate: 13% (Ontario HST) stored in restaurants.tax_rate — use this, never hardcode

